The paper proposes a mechanism for incentivizing honest reports in a setting where participants are asked multiple similar possibly subjective multi-choice questions. This falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The mechanism involves information evaluation and identification of high-quality information, which also relates to machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the use of mutual information, which is a concept in information theory (cs.IT).
